      "content": {
        "title": "Cervical Spine Trauma Injuries",
        "definition": "Subaxial cervical fracture-dislocations, facet injuries, and occipitocervical dissociation classified and managed with SLIC and stability assessment.",
        "summary": "Occipitocervical dissociation is highly unstable. SLIC ≥5 favors surgery for subaxial injuries. Maintain cervical spine precautions until cleared."
